So I can override the view like this:

```python
from oscarapi.views.basket import AddProductView as _AddProductView

class AddProductView(_AddProductView):
    def validate(self, basket, product, quantity):
        # check if there is a orderlimit for this product
        allowed, message = basket.add_product_allowed(product, quantity)
        if not allowed:
            return False, message
        return super(
            AddProductView, self).validate(basket, product, quantity)
```

@tcr3dr The docs system expects comments to be at the top of the file - so all the introduction was being omitted - this moves the imports below the docs so everything works. There were also some errors where whitespace lines after code blocks were missing. 

Worth integrating this sooner rather than later.

I'd also like to move the docs to be alongside the method descriptions (bettter for maintenance) but I want to know I won't be messing with changes you're making to the file before I do that).

